  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Pre-Contract & Tender) #80656",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Construction</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Quantity Surveyor</strong></li><li>Working Location: Jurong West</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days, Monday – Friday (8am – 5.30pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Variable Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support the Tender Manager in drafting tender proposals and cost estimates for both main contract and subcontract work.</li><li>Study and interpret tender documents, drawings, and specifications to highlight key requirements.</li><li>Prepare Requests for Quotation (RFQ) and liaise with subcontractors and suppliers on pricing and technical queries.</li><li>Perform quantity take-off, measurement, and cost evaluation to ensure accurate costing.</li><li>Help compile bid documentation, cost breakdowns, and all relevant submission papers.</li><li>Communicate and follow up with consultants, architects, developers, and contractors on tender-related issues.</li><li>Provide general assistance in contract administration and undertake other duties as assigned.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma in Quantity Surveying, Building, or a related field.</li><li>At least 2-3 years of related experience in the construction industry.</li><li>Knowledge of AutoCAD will be an added advantage.</li><li>Proactive with good analytical and problem-solving skills.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#80656 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
